I'm still trying to figure out what I prefer most:

- Reading my micro.blog followers timeline in a browser on [micro.blog](https://micro.blog);
- Following micro.blog posts through RSS in [Reeder.app](https://reeder.app) or;
- Reading micro.blog posts in a my preferred mastodon client [Ivory](https://tapbots.com/ivory/).

While reading micro.blog posts in Ivory is a joy, there is a downside in replying to them. These replies will come in through my Mastodon account [@camiel@social.lol](https://micro.blog/camiel@social.lol) and not from my [camiel@schoonens.social](https://micro.blog/camiel) micro.blog account which is my preferred account.
